version_description: The chords have been taken by ear and watching some Youtube covers, therefore although it sounds good with a decent amount of distortion is not 100% accurate. The song have an upbeat shuffle feeling. I wrote down the two recurrent riffs but tempo is just approximated. Chords overall are kind of power chords shapes. Just listen to the song and you'll figure it out how to play in a few hours.
Detailed Riff1 one and Riff2, aligned chords to lyrics, added fill lyrics, added chords backing the guitar solo.

This is basically a rhythm guitarist's version. Put the capo on the 2nd fret, and rhythm guitarists can actually play this and back up the lead. It's still in the key of B, but without all the lead riffs.
Basic Chord Structure for the studio recording version of the song. Listen for timing as each chord because many of them strike slightly (1/16th note) before the 1 beat.
Hey folks. I'm not quite sure if there are one or two chords that should be minor. Please feel free to correct me. Have fun.
With correct intro to solo, solo and 7-ens.
Based on Mitski's studio recording, the rhythm at the ending is not consistent, but you can get it by listening to the song.
